HEADWORD: Klicket
<hw>Klick"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Clicket</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A small postern or gate
in a palisade, for the passage of sallying parties.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>klinket</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

